<H2>Races</H2>

<h3>The Problems</h3>
<p>
Dungeons and Dragons standard races make a lot of difference to
starting characters but these differences quickly fade into
insignificance after a few levels.</p>

<p>Many more exotic races have level adjustment penalties for the
significant initial benefits they give. However, this can present
problems for adventures for low levels, and at high levels these races
become underpowered because of the level penalty.</p>

<p>Certain races take attribute penalties (particularly charisma) to
reflect an attitude rather then an actual lack of the attribute. This
has unfortunate consequences in certain skills which the race aught to
be good at, for example, for dwarves, use magical device, or intimdate
for half-orcs.  </p>


<P>
Unearthed Arcana gives a couple of interesting ideas here: one is to
buy off the expensive level adjustments progressively during the
character's career. This works because of the self correcting nature
of the DnD XP system. The first problem is never really addressed, but
the section on Racial Paragons provides an excellent clue which can be
the starting point for solving both problems, along with the racial
progression ideas spelled out in the monster manuals.</p>

<P>
What I propose is to slightly boost all 0LA races, to allow 1LA races
to start at par. Then to address the growing irrelevance of race as
one advances in level by having other benefits kick in as the
character goes up in level.  For races penalized in charisma, I impose
penalties on specific skills instead.</p>

  <h4>Aasimar.</h4>

    <p>Aasimars represent the remnants of an ancient proud lineage.
    An Aasimar character may begin play as level 1 with no ECL
    adjustment.</p>


<table>
<CAPTION><STRONG>Table 1:</STRONG>
Aasimar Racial benefits</CAPTION>
<TR><TH ALIGN="LEFT">Level</TH>
<TH ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP" WIDTH=180>Special</TH>
</TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT">1st</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP" WIDTH=180>Normal aasimar racial benefits, no level adjustment</TD>
</TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT">5th</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP" WIDTH=180>+4 Spot and Listen</TD>
</TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT">10th</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP" WIDTH=180>Improved darkvision (+30 ft), daylight 3/day</TD>
</TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT">15th</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP" WIDTH=180>Cha +2</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

